<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: cloudk</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-08-14 12:45:50</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>I was very lucky with this quest, but kinda paid for it at the same time.  Decided to start with Starshine, well there were only about 400 people on the server at the time so he was uncamped :)  It's just a matter of getting up at a silly time when nobody (with a life) plays. He wasn't there when I arrived, but I only had to wait 2 minutes for him to spawn!<BR>
On to Qeynos, and only it took me 4 tries to get the Jester card. The total cost of 18 gold seems pretty cheap for such a nice item!  I bet if it were droppable, it would go for at least a few hundred pp, since the +10 wis is just sooo nice.<BR>
It did indirectly take me about 7 hours though.  This is because it was late, I was tired, and whilst looking for the smugglers area I got lost.  Some green-con bandits showed up - about 4 of them - and starting whacking me.  I killed 3 and got the other one down to about 5HP, but at the same time I was down to 5 as well, and she won :(<BR>
I did this at level 31, so dying cost me about 7 hours of exp.  Had I decided to get sleep rather than getting online at that time, I would have had the sense to gate - but then Starshine would have been camped ^_^ so it wouldn't matter.</font></td></tr></table>
